#: src\getting-started.md:58
msgid "A few things worth noticing, because they shape the whole API:"
msgstr ""

#: src\getting-started.md:60
msgid ""
"**`Molecule::parse(data, format)`** takes the OpenBabel _format id_ as a "
"string — `\"smi\"`, `\"mol\"`, `\"sdf\"`, `\"pdb\"`, `\"inchi\"`, and so on. "
"The same id set is used by `write`. Parsing returns \\[`Result`\\], and an "
"unreadable input yields \\[`Error::Parse`\\]."
msgstr ""

#: src\getting-started.md:64
msgid ""
"**Methods that read** (`formula`, `molar_mass`, `atoms`, …) take `&self`; "
"**methods that mutate** the molecule (`add_hydrogens`, `generate_3d`, "
"`optimize_geometry`, …) take `&mut self`. This mirrors OpenBabel's own model "
"while giving you Rust's borrow-checker guarantees."
msgstr ""

#: src\getting-started.md:68
msgid ""
"**Fallible operations return `Option` or `Result`.** Many OpenBabel routines "
"signal failure by returning a null/empty result rather than throwing; the "
"safe API surfaces that as `None`/`Err` so you handle it explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: src\getting-started.md:72
msgid "The demo CLI"
msgstr ""

